description: MPs voted to return to Senegal and Benin prized artefacts that were looted during colonial times.
title: French MPs back return of looted African artefacts
title_page: French MPs back return of looted African artefacts - BBC News
maintext: Benin will receive a throne taken in 1892 from the palace of Behanzin, the last king of what was then Dahomey. Senegal will get a sword that belonged to a 19th-Century sheikh.
